          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
        },
        "body": "Hi [~vvasudev], thank you for pointing out YARN-3630. YARN-3630 and this ticket are targeting at different problems.YARN-3630 is trying to slow down the heartbeat in a large cluster in order not to overwhelm the RM, while our angle is trying to inform RM about latest info as soon as possible in order to get better task throughput and lower latency. These two features doesn't conflict and can work together. \n",
